[
    {
        "content": "<p>I just noticed that the binary operator version of <code>?</code> got removed in <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/pull/9618\">PR#9618</a>. Can you explain the reasoning behind that change <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"281383\">@Richard Feldman</span>?</p>\n<p>I quite liked that syntax, it's a very compact way to add descriptive errors:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Diff\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"gd\">-   first_str = strings.first() ? NoFirstError</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+   first_str = match strings.first() {</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+       Ok(s) =&gt; s</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+       Err(e) =&gt; { return Err(NoFirstError(e)) }</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+   }</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I used that syntax a lot in our <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/www.roc-lang.org/blob/1bc41b3701ff93a6c38a926a4de954dea36de5fc/website/build_website.roc#L93\">build_website.roc</a> script (old Roc).</p>",
        "id": 606272733,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1782313526
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wanted to revisit the syntax</p>",
        "id": 606274301,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1782313900
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I admittedly have not thought of any better ideas since <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 606274513,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1782313957
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>maybe it's actually best to put it back then</p>",
        "id": 606274590,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1782313978
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>want to open a pr for that?</p>",
        "id": 606276314,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1782314403
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes. right away</p>",
